<br>
  I asked to join another guilds raid the other night and was basically told no thanks.  They have a staff from an earlier run and are holding it as a trade piece for the Shattered Emerald of Corruption.  Plat bids are up to 125k &lt;sigh&gt;  <br>
<br>
  I'm not angry at the guild or anything like that, I totally understand - I'm just frustrated at being so close to the end of this quest, and disappointed by the unlikelihood of getting to hate enough to see the staffs drop.  I knew this was coming based on the other posts I’ve seen about peeps going to hate umpteen times with no luck.<br>
<br>
How did those who traveled to hate 30+ times do it?  With their own guilds?  Friends?  Or did you just beg for a chance?  It seems to me the likelihood of join another guilds raid is slim to none considering most have their own mages or will use the staff as a bargaining tool for other rare epic drops.<br>
<br>
On Innoruuk, Hate is a scheduled plane with some free for all nights.  I've been looking at the calendar and posting a request on the msg-board of each guild I see going but no luck so far....<br>
